<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,150,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Adult habitus:</emphasis>
Triocellate. General body color pale, yellow to brown in alcohol. Head pale brown, compound eyes black, ocelli greyish with black margins, anterior ocellus paler; an obscure interocellar brown spot present, antennae and palpi light brown (
<figureCitation box="[408,497,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-130@1.[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A. head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, lateral view; D: terminalia, ventral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with a solid median stripe bearing asymmetrical rugosities and covered with dark brown margins (
<figureCitation box="[447,536,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-130@1.[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A. head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, lateral view; D: terminalia, ventral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Thoracic sclerite paler, mesonotum and metanotum have dark brown U-shaped markings; without a dark medial stripe in the middle (
<figureCitation box="[758,848,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1420,1444]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,453,1397]" captionTargetId="figure-151@2.[284,1303,453,1397]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov. A: male abdomen, dorsal view; B: female abdomen, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Wings transparent, legs pale. Abdominal terga 1–8 each bearing brown longitudinal stripes, tergum 1–4 dorsally with triangular stripe and laterally with brown bands, tergum 5–7 with trapezoidal stripe; tergum 8 stripe is rounded and smaller than the other stripes. Cerci pale brown, basal segment brown, terminal segments paler and covered with long setae (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1094,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1420,1444]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,453,1397]" captionTargetId="figure-151@2.[284,1303,453,1397]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov. A: male abdomen, dorsal view; B: female abdomen, dorsal view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="2" pageNumber="62" startId="2.[151,250,1420,1444]" targetBox="[284,1303,453,1397]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1420,1480]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1420,1444]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rehman, Du &amp; Huo" authorityName="Rehman, Du &amp; Huo" authorityYear="2022" box="[287,716,1420,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateoblonga" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[287,494,1420,1444]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Sweltsa lateoblonga</emphasis>
Rehman, Du &amp; Huo
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[725,808,1420,1444]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[725,808,1420,1444]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A: male abdomen, dorsal view; B: female abdomen, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1526,2021]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,269,1527,1553]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Male:</emphasis>
Body length 9.0–10.0 mm, forewing length 7.5–8.0, hindwing length 6.5–7.0 (n = 7). Tergum 9 without any transverse process, anteriorly with paired brown spots and without median excavation on posterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,1598,1625]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-130@1.[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A. head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, lateral view; D: terminalia, ventral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Tergum 10 with a pair of distinct dark brown transverse lateral bands, the medial area of the bands greatly enlarged in the shield-like darkly sclerotized basal anchor; the shield dorsally bears two sclerotized posterolateral arms, the anchor wider than long, and with broad typical trapezoidal membranous groove and paragential plates between hemiterga (
<figureCitation box="[381,470,1706,1733]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-130@1.[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A. head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, lateral view; D: terminalia, ventral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Epiproct is broad, widely oblong, but longer than its basal width; medially slightly constricted, apically broad in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[632,766,1742,1769]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A and B: epiproct, dorsal view; C and D, lateral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
), the basal ring with dorsal and lateral bare areas (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1422,1742,1769]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A and B: epiproct, dorsal view; C and D, lateral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); sclerotized dorsally, dark brown from base to the median area, apically yellowish. Basal sclerite of epiproct bears two oval shape patches; in lateral view, margins are much constricted from the base to the apical third, sub-apically wide and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[371,506,1850,1877]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A and B: epiproct, dorsal view; C and D, lateral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Figs. 3C–D</figureCitation>
). The apex is smooth, bearing a shiny triangular shape cap, but most of the dorsal and ventral surface is covered with golden brown, appressed setae (
<figureCitation box="[902,1038,1886,1913]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A and B: epiproct, dorsal view; C and D, lateral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Figs. 3A–D</figureCitation>
). The aedeagus is completely membranous and subtriangular in shape (
<figureCitation box="[557,644,1922,1949]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-130@1.[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A. head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, lateral view; D: terminalia, ventral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). The dorsal and dorsolateral lobes are slightly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1285,1372,1922,1949]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-130@1.[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A. head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, lateral view; D: terminalia, ventral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). The posterior portion of the aedeagus bears a pair of nipple-shaped lobes mesally, each covered with numerous long hairs (
<figureCitation box="[221,310,1994,2021]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-130@1.[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A. head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, lateral view; D: terminalia, ventral view." pageId="2" pageNumber="62">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1402,1291,1315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" startId="3.[151,250,1291,1315]" targetBox="[219,1368,181,1267]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1402,1291,1315]" box="[151,1402,1291,1315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1291,1315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rehman, Du &amp; Huo" authorityName="Rehman, Du &amp; Huo" authorityYear="2022" box="[281,697,1291,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateoblonga" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[281,486,1291,1315]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Sweltsa lateoblonga</emphasis>
Rehman, Du &amp; Huo
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[703,783,1291,1315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[703,783,1291,1315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male. A and B: epiproct, dorsal view; C and D, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1361,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,296,1361,1387]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Female:</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[444,594,1361,1388]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.05" metricValueMin="0.95" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="10.5" valueMin="9.5">9.5–10.5 mm</quantity>
, forewing length 8.0–9.0 mm, hindwing length 7.5–8.0 mm (n = 9). Habitus is generally similar to the male. Abdominal tergum 1–7 dorsally with medial stripes (
<figureCitation box="[1087,1173,1397,1423]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1420,1444]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,453,1397]" captionTargetId="figure-151@2.[284,1303,453,1397]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov. A: male abdomen, dorsal view; B: female abdomen, dorsal view." pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). The posterior margins of sternum 8 bear a subtriangular subgenital plate ventrally, reaching near the middle of sternum 9; the posterior tip of the subgenital plate is broadly rounded and connected to preceding segments that are slightly incised at the base (
<figureCitation box="[159,294,1505,1531]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1528,1552]" captionTargetBox="[269,1318,417,1504]" captionTargetId="figure-156@4.[269,1318,417,1504]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., female. A: head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, ventral view; D: subgenital plate." pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Figs. 4B–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1361,2036]" box="[199,514,1541,1567]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,396,1541,1567]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Nymph and egg:</emphasis>
Unknown
</paragraph>
