<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="63" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1361,2036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1721,1747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name of the new species refers to the shape of the epiproct that is widely oblong. The Latin “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rehman, Du &amp; Huo" authorityYear="2022" box="[164,298,1757,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateoblonga">
<emphasis box="[164,298,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">lateoblonga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” means widely oblong.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1361,2036]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,393]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1793,1819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Remarks:</emphasis>
The new species is closely similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2009" box="[758,828,1793,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wui">
<emphasis box="[758,828,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">S. wui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tierno de Figueroa &amp; Fochetti, 2002" authorityName="Tierno de Figueroa &amp; Fochetti" authorityYear="2002" box="[887,1433,1793,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnan">
<emphasis box="[887,999,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">S. yunnan</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tierno de Figueroa, J. M. &amp; Fochetti, R." box="[1008,1433,1793,1819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" pagination="93 - 95" refId="ref5729" refString="Tierno de Figueroa, J. M. &amp; Fochetti, R. (2002) Sweltsa yunnan, sp. nov., a new stonefly from China (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae). Oriental Insects, 36, 93 - 95. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2002.10417327" type="journal article" year="2002">Tierno de Figueroa &amp; Fochetti, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The new species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2009" box="[641,709,1829,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wui">
<emphasis box="[641,709,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">S. wui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the head, pronotum pigmentation, and the epiproct. The head of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2009" box="[183,253,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wui">
<emphasis box="[183,253,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">S. wui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears a distinct interocellar triangular spot and the pronotum has a dark median band (fig. 
<quantity box="[1294,1338,1865,1891]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." pageId="3" pageNumber="63" pagination="156 - 163" refId="ref5630" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2009) Sweltsa wui and Haploperla valentinae (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae), two new stoneflies from Sichuan Province, China. Illiesia, 5, 156 - 163." type="journal article" year="2009">Stark &amp; Sivec 2009</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast, the head of the new species lacks a triangular spot and the pronotum bears a solid median line with asymmetrical rugosities (
<figureCitation box="[537,625,1937,1963]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-130@1.[231,1357,669,1941]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A. head and pronotum; B: terminalia, dorsal view; C: terminalia, lateral view; D: terminalia, ventral view." pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). The base of the epiproct of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2009" box="[949,1011,1937,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wui">
<emphasis box="[949,1011,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">S.wui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is broad and rectangular dorsally then constricted from near base to apical third and apically widened (figs. 
<quantity box="[945,1018,1973,2000]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.397" metricValueMax="1.524" metricValueMin="1.27" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" unit="in" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." box="[1026,1255,1973,1999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" pagination="156 - 163" refId="ref5630" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2009) Sweltsa wui and Haploperla valentinae (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae), two new stoneflies from Sichuan Province, China. Illiesia, 5, 156 - 163." type="journal article" year="2009">Stark &amp; Sivec 2009</bibRefCitation>
), while the new species epiproct base is circular, slightly widened towards the apex dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1001,1088,2009,2035]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A and B: epiproct, dorsal view; C and D, lateral view." pageId="3" pageNumber="63">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
) and laterally much constricted almost to two-thirds of the epiproct and wider apically (
<figureCitation box="[781,872,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A and B: epiproct, dorsal view; C and D, lateral view." pageId="4" pageNumber="64">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). The epiproct cap of new species is also different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2009" box="[213,282,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wui">
<emphasis box="[213,282,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">S. wui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The epiproct cap of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2009" box="[525,594,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wui">
<emphasis box="[525,594,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">S. wui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is circular, almost lying above the tip of the epiproct (figs. 6, 
<quantity box="[1296,1340,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I." pageId="4" pageNumber="64" pagination="156 - 163" refId="ref5630" refString="Stark, B. P. &amp; Sivec, I. (2009) Sweltsa wui and Haploperla valentinae (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae), two new stoneflies from Sichuan Province, China. Illiesia, 5, 156 - 163." type="journal article" year="2009">Stark &amp; Sivec 2009</bibRefCitation>
), while the new species with the rounded triangular cap, dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1039,1175,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1291,1315]" captionTargetBox="[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-26@3.[219,1368,181,1267]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Sweltsa lateoblonga Rehman, Du &amp; Huo sp. nov., male. A and B: epiproct, dorsal view; C and D, lateral view." pageId="4" pageNumber="64">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
). The new species also show similar characteristics to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tierno de Figueroa &amp; Fochetti" authorityYear="2002" box="[498,608,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnan">
<emphasis box="[498,608,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">S. yunnan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The epiproct of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tierno de Figueroa &amp; Fochetti" authorityYear="2002" box="[801,911,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnan">
<emphasis box="[801,911,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">S. yunnan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks an apical cap and is almost parallel from the base to the apex (figs. 
<quantity box="[448,519,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" unit="in" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Tierno de Figueroa, J. M. &amp; Fochetti, R." box="[526,964,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" pagination="93 - 95" refId="ref5729" refString="Tierno de Figueroa, J. M. &amp; Fochetti, R. (2002) Sweltsa yunnan, sp. nov., a new stonefly from China (Plecoptera: Chloroperlidae). Oriental Insects, 36, 93 - 95. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2002.10417327" type="journal article" year="2002">Tierno de Figueroa and Fochetti, 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2009" box="[1159,1227,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wui">
<emphasis box="[1159,1227,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">S. wui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tierno de Figueroa &amp; Fochetti" authorityYear="2002" box="[1283,1394,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnan">
<emphasis box="[1283,1394,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">S. yunnan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unknown, while the subgenital plate of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rehman &amp; Huo &amp; Du, 2022" authorityName="Rehman &amp; Huo &amp; Du" authorityYear="2022" box="[590,751,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateoblonga" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[590,751,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">S. lateoblonga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[757,846,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[757,846,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is closely similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhiltzova &amp; Levanidova 1978" authorityName="Zhiltzova &amp; Levanidova" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Chloroperlidae" genus="Sweltsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis box="[1076,1201,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="64">S. insularis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zhiltzova, L. A. &amp; Levanidova, I. M." pageId="4" pageNumber="64" pagination="3 - 29" refId="ref5888" refString="Zhiltzova, L. A. &amp; Levanidova, I. M. (1978) New species of stoneflies (Plecoptera) from the Far East. Trudy Zoologischeskogo Instituta Akademia Nauk, 61, 3 - 29." type="journal article" year="1978">Zhiltzova &amp; Levanidova 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(fig. 
<quantity box="[330,400,366,393]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.29794" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" unit="in" value="511.0">511 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Teslenko, V. A. &amp; Zhiltzova, L. A." box="[406,737,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="64" refId="ref5783" refString="Teslenko, V. A. &amp; Zhiltzova, L. A. (2009) Key to the stoneflies (Insecta, Plecoptera) of Russia and adjacent countries. Imagines and nymphs. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, 382 pp." type="book" year="2009">Teslenko and Zhiltzova 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
